<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-337-520  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 337 520.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  April 7 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer industry should lead recycling effort. (editorial)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryEarth DayEnvironmental Protection.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUTER INDUSTRY SHOULD LEAD RECYCLING EFFORT - Editorial SAUSALITO,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1990 APR 6 (NB) -- This &quot;Open Letter&quot; to the computerindustry arrived in Newsbytes' MCI mailbox today.andP;  We thought we might shareit with you, as we agree with Mr. Batterson's sentiments.andM;DAVID W. BATTERSON 47 CRESCENT AVENUE SAUSALITO, CA  94965andM;415-331-1259  MCI Mail: 273-7218  Internet: dbatterson@mcimail.comandM;OPEN LETTER TO THE COMPUTER INDUSTRYandM;To all hardware/software cos., distributors, PR firms andamp; computerpublications:andM;With Earth Day coming up April 22, what better way to show concern for ourworld than by starting to use recycled paper products.andM;As a writer/reviewer, I don't recall having seen ANY manuals, product sheets,newsletters or presskits that mentioned they were printed on recycled paper.andO;Can you imagine the number of trees it takes just to print the manuals forWordPerfect, Lotus 1-2-3, dBASE and Novell Netware?andM;Are there any companies in our industry using recycled paper? If so, let'sfind out who they are so that we can express our approval.andM;What company plans to start using recycled paper?andP;  Will it be yours?andM;Your input and additional ideas would be appreciated.andP;  Spread the word!andM;Sincerely,andM;David BattersonandM;Editor's note: We could use some names, for those of you who also know goodsources of recycled paper for use in laser printers and dot matrix printers.andO;And on that subject, is there a good source of recyclable fax paper? Thanksin advance to those of you taking the time to respond to this.andP;  We willpublicize the information in an upcoming editorial.andP;  -- Wendy Woods, editorin chiefandM;(Newsbytes/19900406)</TEXT></DOC>